commit.message:
Import Context from django.template.context

It was available as django.template.base.Context for backwards
compatibility but was removed in Django 3.1

Remove CachedStaticFilesStorage and dependent storages in Django >= 3.1

Importing the referenced class was resulting in an ImportError.
CachedStaticFilesStorage has been deprecated since Django 2.2 and was
finally removed in Django 3.1.

PipelineCachedStorage and NonPackagingPipelineCachedStorage are also
made undefined for in this commit.

Django >= 3.1 users should instead use PipelineManifestStorage and
NonPackagingPipelineManifestStorage which make use of
ManifestStaticFilesStorage.

Fixes issue #714

Add auto-releases to django-pipeline.

Fix https://github.com/jazzband-roadies/help/issues/177.

commit.message:
Keep mimetypes as str on all versions of Python.

As noted in jazzband/django-pipeline#297 the mimetypes should not be
`unicode` *on Python 2*. But they should be `str` on Python 3.

Caused by: jazzband/django-pipeline#297
Effecting:
- pallets/werkzeug#636
- pallets/werkzeug#637
Doc: PipelineManifestStorage and MutableMapping import
